.TH GAT-PRUNE 1 "2026-06-04" "gat 0.3.0" "gat Manual"
.SH NAME
gat-prune \- prune stale or merged worktrees
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B gat prune
.RB [ \-\-merged ]
.RB [ \-\-older\-than
.IR days ]
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Always runs
.B git worktree prune
to clear stale administrative metadata. With
.BR \-\-merged ,
additionally removes clean worktrees whose branches are merged into the default
branch. With
.BR \-\-older\-than " " <days> ,
removes worktrees not accessed in that many days (skipping dirty ones unless
.BR \-\-force ).
Both selectors can be combined.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-merged
Remove merged, clean worktrees.
.TP
.BI \-\-older\-than " days"
Remove worktrees unused for N days.
.TP
.BR \-f ", " \-\-force
Include dirty worktrees when pruning by age.
.TP
.BR \-y ", " \-\-yes
Skip confirmation prompts.
.TP
.BR \-n ", " \-\-dry\-run
Show planned pruning only.
.TP
.BI \-\-format " text|json"
Output format.
.SH EXAMPLES
.RS
.EX
gat prune
gat prune \-\-merged \-\-yes
gat prune \-\-older\-than 30 \-\-dry\-run
gat prune \-\-merged \-\-older\-than 60 \-\-yes
.EE
.RE
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR gat (1),
.BR gat\-rm (1),
.BR gat\-doctor (1)
